# Project Conventions

## Tech Stack

- **Runtime**: Bun
- **Framework**: React Router 7 with Cloudflare Workers
- **Styling**: vanilla-extract (type-safe CSS) + Tailwind CSS (utilities)
- **Language**: TypeScript (strict mode)

## Import Conventions

Use absolute imports with the `~` alias for app code:

```typescript
import { vars } from "~/styles";
import { Welcome } from "~/welcome/welcome";
```

## File Naming

- React components: PascalCase (e.g., `Welcome.tsx`)
- Style files: Same name with `.css.ts` extension (e.g., `welcome.css.ts`)
- Utilities/hooks: camelCase (e.g., `useAuth.ts`)
- Route files: lowercase with hyphens (e.g., `home.tsx`, `user-profile.tsx`)

## Component Structure

Colocate component files together:

```
app/
  components/
    Button/
      Button.tsx
      Button.css.ts
      index.ts
```

## Scripts

```bash
bun run dev        # Start development server
bun run build      # Production build
bun run typecheck  # Type checking
bun run deploy     # Deploy to Cloudflare
```
